        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 3:59PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Madisonville to 12
miles southeast of Bedias to near Lake Conroe Dam. Movement was
northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conroe, Huntsville, Crockett, Willis, Madisonville, Austonio,
Trinity, Panorama Village, Cut And Shoot, New Waverly, Coldspring,
Point Blank, Lovelady, Montgomery, Riverside, Huntsville State Park,
Lake Conroe Dam, Crabbs Prairie, Oakhurst, and Evergreen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CST for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
